people don’t usually like what I have to say. that usually doesn’t stop me from saying it. I’ve fought for equality and justice my entire life. even as a white cis male it’s possible to not be a part of the hegemony. being gay marginalizes me from the whole. being asexual severed me from my own community. I stand for what I believe in even when you tell me my existence is wrong. I am not a sin. I will not be silenced.

I’ve been thinking about home a lot lately. With those thoughts comes a tidal wave of emotions. I lost my parents in the same year. Months apart. Everything I thought I knew is wrong and everything now is different but I can’t have those difficult conversations any more. Grieving is hard. Especially when I don’t understand why this hurt so much.
